	<h2 >Basic Terminologies</h2>
	<details>
		<summary>threat</summary>
		<p>An event or action that has got the abiity to compromise system or to voilate security.</p>
	</details>
	<details>
		<summary>exploit</summary>
		<p>way to branch nthe security of machine through a loopm hole.</p>
	</details>
	<details>
		<summary>vulnerability</summary>
		<p>defined as existence of loop hole or weakness in the design or implementation that lead to undesirable,unexpected event that would comprpmise the machine.</p>
	</details>
	<details>
		<summary>attacker</summary>
		<p>any individual who compromises the security of machine illegitimately in order to steal,manipulate or to cause destruction of data.</p>
	</details>
	<details>
		<summary>attack</summary>
		<p>action that is performed by an attacker that would potentially harm the system or information stored in it.</p>
	</details>
	<details>
		<summary>data theft</summary>
		<p>action of information stealin from victims machine.</p>
	</details>
	<details>
		<summary>cookie</summary>
		<p>it is basically the inforemation provided by web server to web client and then sent back by browser each time it accsess that server</p>
	</details>
